# note_tables.h is a GENERATED conformance artifact, not ordinary source: S5NoteTableTest writes it
# with '\n' and then byte-compares the file it reads back against a freshly rendered string. Under
# core.autocrlf=true a checkout would hand it back with CRLF, and the comparison fails — so a FRESH
# CLONE on Windows goes red on a file nobody touched.
#
# Same rule, and the same reason, as testdata/.gitattributes: an artifact that is byte-compared must
# never be EOL-converted. It is stated again here because the rule follows the ARTIFACT, not the
# directory, and this one does not live under /testdata.
note_tables.h -text
